The paper discusses the development of an evaluation dataset for code search using natural language queries, which involves techniques from information retrieval (IR), natural language processing (NLP), software engineering (SE), machine learning (ML), and artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR, which focuses on information retrieval and search engines. Other likely sub-categories include cs.CL (computational linguistics), cs.SE (software engineering), cs.LG (machine learning), and cs.AI (artificial intelligence), which are all relevant to the paper's topic.
